City of South Lake Tahoe News

  1. Caltrans holds open house to prepare public for summer road projects

    CalTrans is inviting the public to come out and learn about three projects scheduled to begin on US 50 in the Lake Tahoe Basin this summer. Read on...

  2. Adult-Use Cannabis application period ends with many applications across categories

    The application process for adult-use cannabis businesses is now complete and the blind screening process will soon begin. Read on...

  3. 'At Lake Level' newsletter debuts

    The City of South Lake Tahoe is pleased to launch its brand new newsletter - "At Lake Level." The monthly newsletter is prepared by City Manager Frank Rush in an effort to keep our community well informed about City issues and initiatives. Read on...

  4. City inspectors working to make local apartment building safe for tenants

    Building inspectors and development services staff conducted a 90-day inspection at a local apartment building today and found that it continues to have unsafe living conditions. Read on...
